<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-08-11T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-08-11T17:00:00-05:00" n="318" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d318">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">868.5151/105: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Greece (<persName type="to">Morris</persName>)</hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-11T18:00:00-04:00">August 11, 1932—6
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>34. Your 79, August 10, 5 p.m. The Department is not clear as to the
                                purpose of your proposed interview with Veniselos but it has no
                                objection to your seeking such an interview if you consider that any
                                useful purpose would be served thereby. If you decide to discuss the
                                matter with Veniselos the Department believes that you might
                                appropriately reiterate the reservation contained in the
                                Department’s 33, August 3, 7 p.m., and repeat the oral statements
                                which you made to the Minister for Foreign Affairs.</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_SHL1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>